# Accepted vulnerabilities for Trivy SBOM scan.
#
# Format: one CVE per line. Optional inline comment after the id.
# Each entry MUST include a justification block above it and a
# re-evaluation date so we do not silently carry stale exceptions.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CVE-2026-41907 / GHSA-w5hq-g745-h8pq -- uuid (npm), severity MEDIUM
#
# CWE-787 (Out-of-bounds Write) + CWE-1285 (Improper Index/Offset Validation)
# in uuid v3/v5/v6 when caller passes an external `buf` argument with an
# out-of-range offset. v4/v1/v7 throw RangeError; v3/v5/v6 silently partial-write.
#
# Why accepted in this repo:
#   - Transitive dependency: @opencode-ai/plugin -> effect@4.0.0-beta.48 -> uuid@13.0.0
#   - This project's source code does not import `uuid` at all
#     (verified with `grep -rn "from 'uuid'\|require.*uuid"` -- zero hits in
#     plugins/, tools/, skills/, prompts/)
#   - No code path passes an external `buf` to v3/v5/v6, so the silent
#     partial-write behaviour cannot be triggered from our code
#   - This repository is a developer configuration bundle, not a runtime
#     service exposed to untrusted input
#
# Re-evaluate by: 2026-08-20 (3 months)
# Remove when: @opencode-ai/plugin upgrades effect past the vulnerable uuid range,
#              or when we can add an npm `overrides` entry without breaking lockfile resolution.
CVE-2026-41907
